Q1 (A) – Short Answers

a) Difference between ping and traceroute
Feature-  	ping	                       traceroute
Purpose-  	Checks connectivity	         Finds path (route)
Output-    	Success/failure + delay	     Each hop (router)
Protocol- 	ICMP	                       ICMP/UDP
Use-       	Basic check	                  Network troubleshooting

b) Steps to identify a phishing email
Check sender email (fake domain)
Look for spelling/grammar mistakes
Avoid clicking unknown links
Check URL before clicking
Look for urgency (“urgent action required”)
Avoid downloading attachments
Verify from official source

c) Function of a switch
Connects devices in LAN
Uses MAC address to forward data
Reduces network collisions
Improves performance (compared to hub)

d) 64-bit WEP key
Requires 10 hexadecimal digits
Examples:
A1B2C3D4E5
1234567890
ABCDEF1234
1A2B3C4D5E
FFFFFFFFFF

f) Banner MOTD (Message of the Day)
Displays a message before login
Used for:
Security warning (unauthorized access prohibited)
Legal notice (acts as evidence)

g) Dummy phishing email + indicators
Example Email:
Subject: Urgent! Your Bank Account Will Be Blocked
Dear Customer,
Your account will be blocked within 24 hours.
Click here to verify: http://fake-bank-login.com
Thank you,
Bank Team
Indicators:
Generic greeting (“Dear Customer”)
Fake/unknown URL
Urgent threat message
Not from official email
Suspicious link


 Q2 (B) – Option 1: Mesh Topology (C Program)

#include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int n, i, j;
    printf("Enter number of nodes: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);
    printf("\nMesh Topology Connections:\n");
    for(i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
        for(j = i + 1; j <= n; j++) {
            printf("Node %d <--> Node %d\n", i, j);
        }
    }
    return 0;
}




















